         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Dear Sir ¶  ¶ I enclose a few cotton pods, from trees growing wild on the Aroona Creek Nor. Ter. ¶  originally propagated from a tree planted by Mr Giles several years ago, there are now several healt...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.07.25a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Bradshaw</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Gossypium barbadense</seg> (MEL 2040538).</p>
               </note>Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose a few cotton pods, from trees growing wild on the Aroona Creek Nor. Ter.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. Northern Territory. All places named by Bradshaw are in NT.</p>
               </note> originally propagated from a tree planted by Mr Giles several years ago, there are now several healthy trees, and when I saw them last month they were masses of snow white cotton, and I thought a sample would interest you. I have not yet been able to collect the baobib nuts for you as they were out of season at the time I was at the Victoria Riv. but I shall take the first opportunity of securing some.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have noticed several tree inscriptions and initials of your old exploring party,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">North Australian Exploring Expedition, 1855-6.</p>
               </note> and the figures are distinct and perfectly legible.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me know if there is anything I can do for you, or any particular specimen you may want</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Joseph Bradshaw</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Palmerston</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Norn Territory</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">July 25th 1894</p>
         </div>
